    "shortDescription": "<p><i>Abeyance</i> suppresses the effects of a single  curse on a creature. It does not restore any damage or drain that might have been caused by the curse. <i>Abeyance</i> cannot suppress curses that cannot be removed by <i>remove curse</i>, but it can suppress curses such as lycanthropy that require <i>remove curse</i> along with additional measures. An individual curse can be suppressed only once by <i>abeyance</i>, even if cast by a different caster.  <i>Abeyance</i> does not allow a creature to divest itself of cursed objects, though it can suppress a curse contracted from an object.</p>",
